parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter gear can cause the starter motor to malfunction, leading to difficulty or inability to start the motorcycle, which can leave the rider stranded.
symptoms: Loud noise or clanking sound when starting the motorcycle
starter gear slips
starter motor spins without engaging
inability to start the motorcycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overcharging of the battery can cause it to leak sulfuric acid, leading to corrosion and damage to surrounding components, and potentially causing a fire. The failure of the rectifier can also cause electrical system malfunctions.
symptoms: Battery leakage
sulfuric acid spill
electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the motorcycle's chain can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The chain snaps or breaks while riding
resulting in loss of power and control
and potentially causing damage to the underside of the motorcycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch rod seal can cause contaminants to enter the clutch system, leading to discoloration of the DOT 4 brake fluid, which can compromise the clutch system and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Discoloration of the DOT 4 brake fluid
clutch system failure
compromised clutch performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tip over sensor bracket can cause the motorcycle to stall or become disabled, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The motorcycle suddenly stalls or becomes disabled
the motorcycle is unable to restart
the tip over sensor bracket is broken or damaged.

symptoms: Brake fluid in the clutch system is contaminated
clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position

vehicle is unable to shift into gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly maintain the brakes can lead to reduced stopping power, increasing the risk of accidents.
